icide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\". Court didn't authenticate, but granted public access.\n\n- FOX report: note may have been written by Epstein, includes text showing farewell tone.\n\n- People report: same, with caveats: not dated, not signed, not verified.\n\n- PBS/AP report: unsealed note, but says unclear who wrote, not mentioned in government reports, separate death-cell note not a suicide note.\n\nBoth sides argue. Need to decide preponderance. We must assess whether evidence shows credible reporting that it was written by Epstein and intended as suicide note.\n\nCredible reporting: multiple outlets (NYTimes request, FOX, People, AP) reported the note as purported suicide note by Epstein, with caveats. The order describes it as \"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\". That is a description, not authentication.\n\nThe rule requires \"credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein\" and \"intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent\". The reporting includes qualifiers \"purported\", \"may have been written\", \"alleged\", \"unclear who wrote\". Does that constitute \"credibly reported\"? The defense argues qualifiers mean not credible. The plaintiff argues that reporting of a note described as suicide note qualifies.\n\nWe must weigh. Preponderance: more likely than not that the public was credibly reported to have been written by Epstein and intended as suicide note.\n\nGiven multiple sources reporting it as \"purported suicide note\", the reporting acknowledges uncertainty, but they still call it a suicide note. The rule says \"credibly reported to have been written...\". The reports are credible; they report the claim. The fact they note uncertainty does not negate that they reported it as a suicide note. So I think preponderance is met.\n\nThus vote \"demonstrated\". Provide brief rationale up to three sentences.\n\nLet's submit.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-8efde9d998c3909d","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Admitted evidence shows a court order unsealing a document described as a \"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\" and multiple credible outlets"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\":\"aar_submit_council_vote\",\"args\":\"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Admitted evidence shows a court order unsealing a document described as a \\\"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\\\" and multiple credible outlets","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782798876269,"responseId":"gen-1782798876-l8HC9d32QIjqUPwwaFe4"}}
