ritten by Epstein and intended as suicide note.\n\nGiven multiple sources reporting it as \"purported suicide note\", the reporting acknowledges uncertainty, but they still call it a suicide note. The rule says \"credibly reported to have been written...\". The reports are credible; they report the claim. The fact they note uncertainty does not negate that they reported it as a suicide note. So I think preponderance is met.\n\nThus vote \"demonstrated\". Provide brief rationale up to three sentences.\n\nLet's submit.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-8efde9d998c3909d","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Admitted evidence shows a court order unsealing a document described as a \"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\" and multiple credible outlets reported the note before the May 8 deadline as a purported Epstein suicide note with farewell language. While reports"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\":\"aar_submit_council_vote\",\"args\":\"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Admitted evidence shows a court order unsealing a document described as a \\\"suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein\\\" and multiple credible outlets reported the note before the May 8 deadline as a purported Epstein suicide note with farewell language. While reports","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782798876269,"responseId":"gen-1782798876-l8HC9d32QIjqUPwwaFe4"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants us to evaluate and vote. We need to consider evidence. The proposition: By May 8, 2026 11:59 PM ET, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by 